[OPTIMA]Booking dimensions availability
resolution description: 4.29-[OPTIMA]-User update : The user cannot create any restrictions. It only requests an availability for certain criteria: - Routing - Date - Commodity - Pieces - Weight - Dimensions - Allocation - etc. Based on the availability response received from Optima, the booking request is made. Therefore, if there is any restriction in Optima for the dimensions of the request, it should not offer availability to the user or at least inform of such restriction. 4.28-[OPTIMA]-Final Chaser has been sent to the user 4.26-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.20-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.19-[OPTIMA]-AFLS updated the following : We have checked the user reported issue and understand that when performing the availability search for MIL - ORD and the length given in the request is 330. And when performing the booking for MXP - ORD the length given in the request is 362.But the user expectation is to reject the booking due to no large booking options for ORD. In OPTIMA we can restrict the bookings based on the length ,width ,height ,MAX_NBR_PIECES ,MAX_WT_PER_PIECE , MAX_SUM_W_L_H by using the PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction. When we were checking for the restriction for the ORD by matching the above attributes we couldn't see PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction created for ORD. Can you please ask the user to create a PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction for ORD to restrict the large bookings ? 4.16-[OPTIMA]-The local office informed the customer that there were no large booking options for ORD, however, those options were shown to the user as available, so the customer asks us if the availability is wrong. Currently pending with AFLS 4.15-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.13-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.9-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.7-[OPTIMA]-Below update from AFLS has been shard with the user : ____________________________________ From the above ticket, we understand that this booking made with the dimensions L x W x H 362x90x299 and booking has been accepted, but the expectation is to reject due to the size of the cargo. Please let us know if our understanding is correct or please explain in detail the issue which you are facing. Could you please check and advise us accordingly ? 4.6-INC20589740 raised at AFLS's end

RS_APT_CONNTIME_KEY OWNER_CODE AIRPORT_CODE EQUIVALENT_AIRPORT_CODE ROUTE_POS_CODE TYPE_OF_AIRCRAFT ORIGIN_GROUP DEST_GROUP CARRIER_GROUP_CODE PRODUCT_GROUP_CODE SPH_GROUP_CODE COMMODITY_GROUP_CODE UN_GROUP_CODE PERIOD_BEGIN_DT PERIOD_END_DT FREQUENCY LOOSE_MIN_CONNECTION_TIME LOOSE_MAX_CONNECTION_TIME UNIT_MIN_CONNECTION_TIME UNIT_MAX_CONNECTION_TIME 4984 BA LHR LHR T F XPS ######## ######## 1234567 239 4320 179 4320 6493 BA LHR LHR T A6F F ######## ######## 1234567 359 2880 359 2880 1 st one got matched based the PRODUCT_GROUP and the LOOSE_MIN_CONNECTION_TIME is 239 mins is around 4 hours. 2nd one is got matched based on the AIRCRAFT_TYPE and the minimum connection time is 359 mins is around 6 hours. resolution description: 4.28-[OPTIMA]-Chaser sent to Jason 4.26-[OPTIMA]-pending with Jason to recreate the scenario 4.20-[OPTIMA]-Information shared with user and AFLS 4.16-[OPTIMA]-Updates from CIBER have been shared with the suppliers 4.15-[OPTIMA]-AFLS have checked the reported flight IB 6621/17-Apr-21 and could see the 075 booking cancellations with this flight via BFE. As mentioned by Simon, this is a known issue and he has advised users to avoid using cancel AWB in BFE. AFLS already had a live session with Jason to perform this scenario in E2E1. Jason has performed the below steps : ?Created a booking via BFE with 125 prefix and IB flight. ?Once the booking confirmed checked the details in OPTIMA and CIBER end and the details has been updated as expected. Then cancelled the booking via BFE and the inventory has been reduced at both OPTIMA and CIBER end. For 075 prefix he faced an issue in creating a booking. AFLS is currently waiting for Jason to test IB booking in E2E1. @Jason Cook : Please advise if we need to have another working session with AFLS . 4.13-[OPTIMA]- INC20434337 has been raised in AFLS's SNOW. new examples have been reported 4.9-Pending with AFLS 4.6-[OPTIMA]-User is unable to test a booking on UAT. We have asked the user to please retry and let us know if you can run a test now ? If still unable, we will ask AFLS to check and advise. 3.30-[OPTIMA]-Simon advised that this is happening due to the IB users trying to use CANCEL AWB which is causing this issue to have mismatch between Optima and CIBER on the booked values and we were advised to check with Jason to check the same in UAT environment. Jason performed a 075 booking on IB flight and tried to CANCEL AWB from IE browser to see the impact. Although it seems to have worked for 125 booking on IB flight from Jason even though AFLS had received error in response from CIBER as below: <OrigMsgInd>X</OrigMsgInd> <MessageSeqNo>1</MessageSeqNo> <RequestStn>HDQ</RequestStn> <UserId>U693908</UserId> <DutyCode>RE</DutyCode> </MessageHead> <Response> <RespInd>E</RespInd> <RespComments>UNABLE TO PROCESS</RespComments> </Response> <AWB_ID> <Prefix>125</Prefix> <Number>30033006</Number> Could you please keep us informed if many users are still seeing this issue? We have been informed that Simon has advised users to avoid using cancel AWB in BFE. [OPTIMA]:[OPTIMA]:INC20434337 raised with suppliers Assigned SNOW ticket ref. no. INC0178533

resolution description: 4.28-[OPTIMA]-Chaser sent to AFLS 4.26-[OPTIMA]-Chaser sent to AFLS 4.19-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 4.15-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 4.13-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 4.9-[OPTIMA]-Chaser sent to AFLS 4.6-[OPTIMA]-AFLS have performed the below steps in our local environment to check the user reported issue. Steps performed in AFLS local environment: Created Part P booking with two segment flight. After created the Part P suffix performed multiple booking amendments in Part P suffix. Created a Part A suffix with the two segment flight. Evaluate the booking and the booking got accepted. Once the Part booking got accepted sent a SSN message for the same without suffix information. In the part booking screen both suffixes information was shown. Since we have sent the SSN with out suffix information, the suffix information & item type information alone blank and all other information remains same. Now we are checking with our internal team to identify if it is working as expected or a defect and we will keep you posted on updates. 3.30-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 3.26-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent the suppliers 3.22-[OPTIMA]-update from AFLS :Initially the booking was created from part booking screen with suffix P and after the multiple amendments in Part P , Part A was created on 2/25/2021 13:14. Later on the 7th version of the booking (25-FEB-21 14:44:23) the SSN came into OPTIMA without a suffix information. Please refer to the below SSN message from CIBER. "QK XXXXXXX .YYYYYYY 144400 SSN/1 25FEB2021/1544+060 MWB/N/125-86107044/STN-FRA RTG/FRASAL CMD/PHARMA ITN/IB9106/27FEB/FRAMAD/SS//K8000T4MC44.000 ITN/IB6343/02MAR/MADSAL/SS//K8000T4MC44.000 SPH/A/ACT/A/ULD USR/001AARS/QLM CUS/23470410213/KUEHNE NAGEL AG CO. PRI/999999" Due to the above SSN message on 7th version the booking was changed from part booking to simple booking . 3.18-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 3.12-Update from CIBER has been shared with AFLS 3.9-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 3.3.-[OPTIMA]-AWBs received from AVCD and we have now shared the same with the user to try on e2e1 3.3-[OPTIMA]-We have asked AVCD team to let us know the 075 AWBs for user to test. 2.26-[OPTIMA]-We had a meeting with users and AFLS, users to replicate this scenario on non-live 2.25-[OPTIMA]-Meeting has been setup for tomorrow at 1200 GMt 2.25-[OPTIMA]-Updates from user have been shared with the suppliers 2.17-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 2.15-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 2.4-[OPTIMA]-User updated the following : "It was rejected and we tried to re-book it again which is impossible in Optima. The part1 gets corrupted. The only option to book is to bypass Optima and book it with Ciber. Not even that works all of the time" It has been shared with the supplier. 2.3-[OPTIMA]-User query has been shared with the suppliers 2.3-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the user 1.28-[OPTIMA]-INC19564934 has been raised at AFLS's end

resolution description: It was identified that "null@cybersource.com" is coming for the PNR, which do not have an email. For these cases, as Cybersource indicates, the email field cannot be empty, since it would give an ERROR, so "null@cybersource.com". appearing. yes We have noticed very in cases email id is appearing but in the line "SSR CCTM" . Hence it is not possible to pick up and present. So this case can be closed as working as design
